Three young Iranians, accused of offending "public  decency" and causing disturbances, were publicly flogged in central Iran,  newspapers said here Sunday.
Two of the accused, whose offences were not specified, each received 60  lashes of the whip during the noon prayers Friday in the city of Saveh, some  100 kilometers (70 miles) southwest of Tehran.
The third was whipped 30 times.
